  "prompt": "Does water exist on mars?",
  "response": "Yes, water exists on Mars, primarily in the form of ice. Polar ice caps composed of water and dry ice (frozen carbon dioxide) are located at both the north and south poles of Mars. Additionally, there is evidence of water ice mixed with the soil just below the Martian surface at various locations across the planet. Space missions have also detected features that suggest the presence of liquid water in the form of briny, salty water during certain times of the year, although this remains a subject of ongoing research and debate.",
